texx - a digital drafting agent

The goal is to create an interface to create and manipulate complex mathematical drafts.
I am inspired by the mathematical drafts of Bateman and Griswold.
I someday hope to make this freely accessible from my website, or just make it a website on its own.


Functions:
- nice GUI for drafting, like AdaCAD
    - click to toggle threading, tie-up, and treadling.
    - change colors
- import/export .WIF or .pdf file formats
- save/copy threadings, tie-ups, treadlings, etc
- save python functions/mathematical equations that generate complex treadlings, threadings, etc.

